{"blocks":[{"key":"d8cii","text":"Make a 1% molecular grade agarose gel using 1x fresh TAE. Microwave until the agar has just dissolved.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6v293","text":"Note. 100ml for running 25 samples, 35ml for 13 samples","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"319h8","text":"Pour into setup gel tray, add comb and leave for half an hour or until set.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4m66f","text":"Place the set gel into the gel tank (make sure the wells are at the negative end).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8mjfa","text":"Fill the tank with waste TAE until entire gel is submerged - can top up with fresh TAE if needed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ehs16","text":"Load 2-5µl of sample into each well including a 1kb ladder and negative controls","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"am9hc","text":"After gel is run gently lift the tray out of the tank and movie it onto a sybersafe tray view bands in the gel viewer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"6dl0m","text":"Aliquot 9µl of master mix into individual PCR tubes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5prvo","text":"Centrifuge samples briefly (just a few seconds) in a benchtop centrifuge to ensure they are at the bottom of the tube. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
